# Merge review (cross-model)

Before any agent self-merge, a **merge review** MUST run on a model that is **stronger than**,
or (for top-tier implementers) a **peer-tier different family from**, the model that wrote the
code. Same-model or weaker-model “review” does not satisfy this gate.

## When

After: implementation + self-review clean + PR open + **CI green**.
Before: `gh pr merge` / self-merge under `loop-workflow.mdc`.

Spec-only / docs PRs still get a merge review (lighter checklist), unless **all** of:
- ≤20 changed lines total, and
- changes are docs/comments only, and
- **no** edits to `.cursor/rules/**`, `AGENTS.md`, workflow YAML, or executable code

Then note `merge-review: skipped (trivial)` in the PR and proceed. Process-rule changes like
this file never qualify for the skip.

## Reviewer model (stronger, or peer cross-family)

Prefer, in order, the strongest available that is **not** the implementer’s model family:

1. `claude-opus-4-8-thinking-medium` (or latest Opus thinking slug available)
2. `claude-opus-4-7-thinking-medium`
3. `gpt-5.6-terra-medium` / `gpt-5.6-sol-medium` / `gpt-5.5-medium`

| Implementer (approx.) | Reviewer MUST be |
|---|---|
| Composer / Auto / `composer-*` | Opus (preferred) or GPT-5.6 tier |
| Sonnet / `claude-sonnet-*` / `claude-4.6-sonnet-*` | Opus |
| GPT-5.x medium | Opus (preferred) or a different GPT high-tier if Opus unavailable |
| Opus (Opus wrote the code) | GPT-5.6 tier — **peer cross-family** (satisfies the gate) |
| Gemini / Grok / any other family | Opus (preferred), else GPT-5.6 tier |
| Unknown / unlisted | Opus (preferred), else GPT-5.6 tier |

If no eligible reviewer model can be launched (tooling failure), **do not self-merge**: label
`needs-human`, comment that merge-review could not run, and wait.

Launch via the Task tool (`subagent_type: generalPurpose`, `readonly: true` for the review pass)
with an explicit `model:` slug from the list above. Do not “review yourself” in the same turn and
call it a merge review.

## Reviewer brief (give the subagent all of this)

- PR URL / branch / `git diff origin/main...HEAD`
- Spec path + acceptance criteria (if any)
- What the implementer believes is done
- Ask for a structured report only:

```text
## Verdict
approve | approve-with-fixes | block

## Findings
For each finding:
- severity: must-fix | should-fix | nit | ambiguous
- location: path:line (if known)
- issue: …
- recommendation: …

## Ambiguities for human
(only decisions that need product/security/legal judgment — not style nits)

## Summary
1–3 sentences
```

Review focus: correctness vs spec/acceptance criteria, security/privacy, provenance gaps,
destructive/irreversible risk, missing tests, silent behavior changes. Skip drive-by style
rewrites unless they hide a bug.

## Implementer response (mandatory)

1. **must-fix** / **should-fix** → implement on the PR branch, push, re-run lint/typecheck/tests.
2. **nit** → optional; skip unless cheap.
3. **ambiguous** → do **not** guess. Comment on the PR + issue with the decision needed, apply
   `needs-human`, and **stop** (no self-merge).
4. If the reviewer **blocks** or leaves unresolved must-fix items → no self-merge until fixed
   or human clears them.
5. After non-trivial fixes, run **one** follow-up merge review (same stronger model). Cap at
   two review rounds; if still contested → `needs-human`.

## Durable trail + PR attestation

1. Post the reviewer’s **full structured report** as a **PR comment** (auditable; not only a
   private chat). Prefer attributing the comment to the review (model slug in the comment body).
2. PR body (or a follow-up comment before merge) MUST include:

```markdown
## Merge review
- Reviewer model: `<slug>`
- Implementer model: `<slug or "session/auto">`
- Verdict: approve | approve-with-fixes (then fixed) | block → needs-human
- Review comment: <required URL of the PR comment that contains the structured report>
```

`Review comment` MUST be a GitHub comment URL on this PR. A pasted summary alone is **not**
enough. Self-merge is forbidden without this attestation (except the trivial skip note above).

## Relationship to self-review

Self-review (same agent, up to 3 passes) remains required and is **not** a substitute for
merge review. Order: implement → self-review → PR → CI green → **merge review** → fix/escalate →
merge.
